      "content": "When addressing global standards, it's important to acknowledge that cultural norms heavily influence what \"top tier\" means. In many parts of Asia, for instance, modesty in dress and deference to seniority are paramount, often requiring more conservative coverage than in Western settings. In parts of Nigeria, vibrant fabrics and a strong sense of personal presentation are highly valued expressions of status. Tailoring these local values into a global guide means emphasizing respect for hierarchy and adapting formality to the specific cultural context of the meeting.",
